{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01X2yuRa158Zynd1jQaRS98T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now understand the vulnerability. In `SignedPublicKeysTrustValidatorImpl.isTrusted()`, line 45 calls `ecdsa.verify(signatureDer)` but **discards its boolean return value**. `Signature.verify()` returns `false` for a well-formed-but-invalid signature (it only throws `SignatureException` for malformed encoding). Since the result is ignored, the method unconditionally returns `true` at line 56 — so any forged signature with valid DER encoding is accepted as trusted. This is the CWE-295 improper certificate validation.\n\nThe fix is to return the result of the signature verification:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3315,"cache_read_input_tokens":20758,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3315},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6183964c-9647-4a16-826d-bb8501aede2b","uuid":"a05c80dc-e058-4557-9894-a37d10e4383c","request_id":"req_011Cca4TTnUUJ8zvNrqBkSxv"}
